title: [Wormwood Slough, Boggy Trail]
description: Black water seeps from the spongy ground to the south where the path dips.  Blighted trees provide little shade and no color, their limbs greyed by a layer of the same mud that covers everything in sight.  A bedraggled trio of carrion birds squabble over a rancid and unrecognizable meal.
